AUDIO: 'Hello ladies and gentlemen, it\'s Mike here at Gay for Scratch and today we are looking at a version of the GDAU editor which is actually better in a lot of ways, at least in my humble opinion and then way worse in the fact that well it\'s not part of the official repository'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'and it\'s not open source. But if you\'re willing to live with those facts, uh GD Studio is definitely worth checking out. You see it in front of you. This is basically a redesign of GDAU, the editor side of GDAU. and he\'s fixed some uh'

[00:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'things that I have found as irritations and obviously he found his irritations as well which is why he went ahead and created this project. Now this is not competing with GDAU. It is a replacement front end. It should stay more or less'

[00:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'compatible with the GDO engine projects behind the scenes. So if you\'re using uh GDO 4.6, there is a 4.6 version. There is a 4.7 version out there available as well. Uh so you can still open your GDO'

[00:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'projects up. This is just a new front-end editor for it. So, why why go through this work? Well, one of the immediate things is it loads faster, and it really does. I found it about twice as fast, which is nice. That\'s definitely something that I appreciate.'

[01:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'But the biggest thing is going to be the UI redesign. So, what you\'re going to notice right now here we have uh just a typical scene. You\'re going to notice the uh side has been collapsed down. I can open that back up, close it down to my heart\'s content. Now, where this really starts to shine though is when we'

[01:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'start talking about multiple scenes. So, right now, you can open up a single scene. You can have multiple tabs. But what you can do with this is I can actually take this tab, by the way, I can drag and drop to position tabs like so. Nothing really special there, but I'

[01:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'can actually take this tab, break it off, and then dock it. So, yes, you can have multiple scenes, different scenes open at the same time on screen at once. And again, each one gets its own'

[01:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'treeview. So, we can go ahead and open it up. So, if you\'re working this, this alone, this should be in GDAU. This is wonderful. I absolutely love this. I don\'t know what the technical'

[01:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'limitations preventing this are, but I have dreamed of this since the very first time I opened up GDAU. This is a huge timesaver and would be one of the biggest usability perks that you could add to GDAU in my humble opinion. Now,'

[02:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL: 
AUDIO: 'it doesn\'t end there. There\'s a bunch more going on behind the scenes. They\'ve also gone ahead and done this. So, now all of the the dropups and so on from the bottom, uh you can now uh pop them up in the middle of the screen like so. Uh at the same time, let\'s say we\'ve got'

